    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="u-bootupgrade">U-Boot Upgrade</h2>

<ol><li>Connect to the debug serial on the board in order to monitor U-Boot output.
<li>Create a single partition formatted ext2, ext3, or FAT on a micro SD card.
<li>Download <a href="/os/imx6/boundary-upgrade.tar.gz">the bootloader upgrade tarball</a> and extract it onto the SD card.
<li>Insert the SD card into the slot on the top of the board, and apply 5V power.
<li>U-Boot will now read the upgrade script and flash the SPI NOR flash with the new U-Boot version.
<li>After it's finished writing, it will read back and verify the flash and let you know it has succeeded.
</ol>

<h2 id="sdcardcreation">SD Card Creation</h2>

<ol><li>Create a single partition formatted ext4 on a micro SD card.
<li>Download <a href="/os/ArchLinuxARM-boundary-latest.tar.gz">the root filesystem tarball</a> and extract it (as root, not with sudo) to the ext4 partition on the SD card. It is important to do this as root, as special files need to be created as part of the filesystem that can only be created by root.
<pre>bsdtar -xpf ArchLinuxARM-boundary-latest.tar.gz -C mountpoint</pre>
<li>Safely unmount the card, and insert it into the slot on the top of the board.
<li>Apply 5V power.
<ul><li>Login as the default user <i>alarm</i> with the password <i>alarm</i>.
<li>The default root password is <i>root</i>.</ul>
</ol>

